  <Fragment slot="extra-sections">
    <section>
      <h2 id="brew-optimization">Brew optimization mini-guide</h2>
      <p>AeroPress is forgiving, but it is not magic. A great bean still tastes rough if your grind is all over the place or your brew runs too hot for the roast you picked. The easiest starting point is 14 to 17 grams of coffee, 220 to 250 grams of water, medium-fine grind, and about 90 seconds of contact time before the press.</p>
      <p>If you are brewing a lighter bean like Araku Ember or Peet’s Big Bang, you can push the water a little hotter and the brew a little longer. If you are using darker beans like Blue Tokai Vienna Roast or Mayorga Café Cubano, cooler water and a slightly shorter steep usually keep the cup sweeter and less bitter.</p>

      <HeroSteps
        title="AeroPress recipe starting point"
        subtitle="Three simple moves that make most beans taste better right away"
        steps={[
